cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the performance of autonomous learning in robots, specifically in a tendon-driven leg with two joints and three tendons. The paper discusses the implementation of the General-to-Particular (G2P) autonomous learning algorithm and the addition of simple kinematic feedback to enhance learning. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
